# FDR ToDo and Done

- **Feature specs (FDRs)** live in `docs/FDRs/ToDo/`. Each file describes one feature with "How it works", "How to test", and "Acceptance criteria".
- When a feature is **fully implemented** (all acceptance criteria satisfied), **move** the FDR file from `docs/FDRs/ToDo/` to `docs/FDRs/Done/` (keep the same filename). That is the only workflow transition agents should use for **delivered** work.
- **Do not delete** FDRs; do not duplicate them. For active delivery, **ToDo → Done** is the only transition.
- **`docs/FDRs/Closed/`** (if present) holds **archived / discarded** specs that were **not** developed to completion. It is **not** a step toward Done and agents must **not** move work there as part of implementation. Humans may park rejected ideas there to avoid re-numbering conflicts; agents only use **ToDo** and **Done** for the live lifecycle.
- Dependencies between features are described in the project's feature list document (e.g. `docs/05 - Feature List.md`); implement in dependency order when possible.
